RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIG PRANKSTER broke very fast and went straight to the front then angled in early, showed the way down the backstretch, dictated terms in the two path on the turn, responded well when shaken up in upper stretch and drew off under a very mild hand ride to win handily. SOLO EMPIRE was last to commence then ridden along on the outside, went five wide on the turn, dropped inward in upper stretch and was no factor. UPTOMYKNEESINIT chased the pace while just behind the leader, checked sharply while lugging out into the turn, went around that bend in the two path under a right-handed crop, angled out into upper stretch, remained on his inside lead in the drive and came up empty. PERNO was hustled from the gate, raced just off the pace, tossed his head and was taken back while keen under tight restraint at the nine-sixteenths, dropped further back leaving the backstretch, was roused three wide on the turn, floated six wide into upper stretch, remained on his inside lead in the drive and had nothing left. FRANKIE R. bumped with a rival at the start, dropped back under some urging, went two to three wide on the turn and failed to respond. HAIR ON FIRE broke in at the start, climbed into kickback while urged at the rear, moved from the rail to the three path on the turn, came six wide into upper stretch and showed little.

DOMESTIC PRODUCT was hard held while saving ground on the first turn then rated just off the pace, moved from the rail to the two path on the far turn then was roused while shifting three wide later on that bend, pursued the leader into upper stretch and capitulated. RACE.RACE_TEXT: Cigar Mile H. - Grade2 AQUEDUCT RACE 10 1M Dirt CR: 111. Stakes Purse 500000. A HANDICAP FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Non-Lasix Race pursuant to 4043.2 (7)(e)(5) Lasix not permitted within 48 hours of post time. By subscription of $500 each which should accompany the nomination; $3,000 to pass the entry box and an additional $4, 500 to start. For horses not originally nominated, a supplemental nomination payment of $2,500 in addition to the entry and starting fees may be made at any time prior to the publication of weights. The purse to be divided 55% to the owner of the winner,2 0% to second, 12% to third, 6% to fourth, 4% to fifth and 3% divided equally amongst the remaining finishers. The first three finishers of the Forty Niner will have their fees waived for the Cigar Mile. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner. Cll osed Saturday, November 18, with 19 Original Nominations and 1 Supplement.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HOIST THE GOLD established the front shortly after the start and showed the way in hand just off the inside under some pressure from PIPELINE to the outside while putting down swift splits, began to shake off that rival through the latter portion of the turn given a notch to work with, got set down spinning just off the inside into upper stretch, drew clear under a drive to the eighth pole, held well and clear to the finish. SENOR BUSCADOR settled just off the inside at the tail of the field early on through the opening half mile, began to advanced thereafter coming under coaxing three furlongs out, angled out eight wide into upper stretch, closed well outside to be along clear of the rest for the place honors. CASTLE CHAOS five then four wide in pursuit, came under coaxing at the three-eighths, swung five wide into upper stretch, dug in under a drive and weakened in the late stages while just holding on for the show honors. THREE TECHNIQUE chased four to five wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, angled seven wide into upper stretch, improved position through to the finish just missing for the show honors on the wire. COASTAL MISSION broke in at the start and came under hustling, chased along the inside and was placed in tight by PIPELINE tucking from the outside while along the rail, balked for a stride or two along the fence five furlongs from home forcing EVERSO MISCHIEVOUS to steady out, came under coaxing at the three-eighths, continued along the inside into upper stretch and weakened. OFFALY COOL four then three wide in pursuit, came under coaxing at the three-eighths, swung three wide into upper stretch, weakened. DR ARDITO chased three then two wide coming under coaxing three furlongs from home, angled six wide at the head of the stretch, offered no response. HIGH OAK chased four then three wide under coaxing from midway on the turn, angled out nine wide into upper stretch, had no response. PIPELINE pressed the pace of HOIST THE GOLD from the outside three wide, got placed to coaxing near the five-sixteenths, continued three wide into upper stretch remaining prominent until straightened away, then tired through to the finish. ACCRETIVE six paths off the inside down the backstretch, went five wide through the turn coaxed along from the three-eighths, cornered six wide into upper stretch and tired. EVERSO MISCHIEVOUS chased just off the inside among rivals, got placed in tight when a pair of foes tucked in from the outside and was forced to steady out five furlongs from home losing about a length and a half of ground, tucked inside and came under coaxing at the seven-sixteenths, cut the corner into upper stretch in retreat and faltered. CASCAIS chased two to three wide down the backstretch and then four wide through the turn pushed along from the three-eighths, continued four wide into upper stretch and folded.
